ll},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"legalrobot","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1878187,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugInformative","message":"Thanks for the report! Email addresses, in general, do allow special characters like `!#$%\u0026'*+-/=?^_`{|}~`. These may not be valid addresses for Gmail specifically, but these special characters are permitted per the email spec (RFC 5322, I think?).\n\nFor the other fields, we also allow special characters since some names can legitimately contain these characters. For example, the name François St. John has both a c-cedilla and a period. These other fields are also non-sensitive.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-07-30T16:06:30.831Z","updated_at":"2017-07-30T16:06:30.831Z","actor":{"username":"danrubins","cleared":false,"url":"/danrubins","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/021/222/c1d0d51f40e0c570e2153b6801fe54c997c757f0_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"legalrobot","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1878207,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi,\nThanks for your response. I think yahoo, hotmail and others popular mail service provider don't allow users to set special characters as e-mail address.  And for other fields (job title, company name) some special characters may be allowed but some should be restricted to use like ``{~^\u003e\u003c\\/*}]``, as these symbol are not a part of a name. Please have a look into this again.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-07-30T16:24:46.268Z","updated_at":"2017-07-30T16:24:46.268Z","actor":{"username":"smziaurrashid","cleared":false,"url":"/smziaurrashid","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-ph